 exclude a significant portion of the brane tension-mass\nparameter space in the $0.1-60$ TeV branon mass range, and up to tensions of\n$\\sim 10$ TeV. More importantly, CTA will significantly enlarge the region\nalready excluded by AMS and CMS, and will provide valuable complementary\ninformation to future SKA radio observations. We conclude that CTA will possess\npotential to constrain brane-world models and, more in general, TeV DM\ncandidates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Jun 2020 12:00:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 26 Oct 2020 17:51:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-27"}
